    <text>
        <body>
            <div frus:doc-dateTime-max="1938-10-15T15:00:00-05:00"
                frus:doc-dateTime-min="1938-10-15T15:00:00-05:00" n="91"
                subtype="historical-document" type="document" xml:id="d91">
                <note rend="inline" type="source">693.116/156 Suppl.: Telegram</note>
                <head>
                    <hi rend="italic">The <gloss type="from">Secretary of State</gloss> to the First
                        Secretary of Embassy in China</hi> (<persName type="to">
                        <hi rend="italic">Salisbury</hi>
                    </persName>), <hi rend="italic">at Peiping</hi>
                </head>
                <opener>
                    <dateline rendition="#right">
                        <placeName>
                            <hi rend="smallcaps">Washington</hi>
                        </placeName>, <date calendar="gregorian" when="1938-10-15T15:00:00-05:00"
                            >October 15, 1938—3 p.m.</date>
                    </dateline>
                </opener>
                <p>284. Department’s October 13, 4 p.m., in regard to importation of radio
                    equipment. Please inform the Japanese Embassy that the proposed <pb facs="0077"
                        n="73" xml:id="pg_73"/> arrangements are not satisfactory and that the
                    Japanese Foreign Office is being so notified; also that it is assumed of course
                    that the proposals do not signify any alteration of the provisional régime’s
                    previous decision to permit importation of American radio equipment for which
                    bona fide orders were placed prior to imposition of the embargo, as expressed in
                    the instruction quoted in the letter addressed by the Superintendent of Customs
                    to the American Consul General at Tientsin under date of September 13.<note
                        n="9" xml:id="d91fn9">In telegram No. 626, October 17, 4 p.m., the Embassy
                        in China at Peiping reported that action was taken the same day
                        (693.116/165).</note>
                </p>
                <p>Repeat to Tokyo, Chungking, Shanghai and Tientsin.</p>
                <closer>
                    <signed>
                        <hi rend="smallcaps">Hull</hi>
                    </signed>
                </closer>
            </div>
        </body>
    </text>
